(x,y)
(a,v)=(x,x-y)
u_x=u_a+u_v
u_y=-u_v
u_a=2u
u(a,v)=C(v)e^{2a}
C(v)
a
u(x,0)=h(x)=C(x)e^{2x}\Rightarrow C(x)=h(x)e^{-2x}
u(x,y)=C(x-y)e^{2x}.
u(x,y)=h(x-y)e^{2y}.
\dfrac{dy}{dt}=1
y(0)=0
y=t
\dfrac{dx}{dt}=1
x(0)=x_0
x=t+x_0=y+x_0
\dfrac{du}{dt}=2u
u(0)=f(x_0)
u(x,y)=f(x_0)e^{2t}=f(x-y)e^{2y}
u(x,0)=h(x)
f(x)=h(x)
\therefore u(x,y)=h(x-y)e^{2y}
